race.comment: Doubt there's much between the better ones. TAUPE (12) is a leader who appeals most, building on his narrow defeat at Kilmore. Keeps Stackhouse and will keep improving for a top metro stable. Will take plenty of catching dropping back 100m. FORT OF DREAMS (2) debuts and is also in elite hands. Has the inside gate and the rail to guide him around. Has looked good at the jumpouts. TOO MUCH TOO SOON (13) resumes and was last seen in Adelaide in a CL1. He was nudged out in an Open two at Sandown-Hillside the one before, and that's good form. ITAZURA (3) has been off the scene for 389 days but showed plenty on debut. Has been gelded and has had a string of jumpouts. Placed the latest, and it won't surprise if he races well. FLAT CHAT (6) has been off the scene for a year, but he has plenty of ability, and the jumpouts have been good. Keep safe.
